{"id":"project-LICHEN-c1k0","title":"ProxyResource catches CancelledError","description":"File: python/src/lichen/coap/resources.py:228-230

The proxy exception handler catches all exceptions including asyncio.CancelledError:
```python
try:
    response = await asyncio.wait_for(
        self._mesh_ctx.request(fwd).response,
        timeout=self._timeout,
    )
except Exception:
    return Message(code=BAD_GATEWAY)
```

This suppresses task cancellation, preventing clean shutdown. When the server is stopping, cancelled proxied requests will return BAD_GATEWAY instead of propagating the cancellation.

